page.title: 15ECOLOGY _ CHIGNALS
page.content:
The area is mainly of arable farming with a few areas of woodland. The footpaths vary from being well maintained to overgrown in a few localities where wild flowers may be observed. The wildlife consists of field dwelling fauna and woodland birds. Waterfowl can be in seen the area due to the large number of small reservoirs, ponds and moats to be found. Many hedge-rows have been removed thereby destroying a potential plethora of natural fauna and flora.
